35/**
36* Encode the given symbol info to a bit matrix.
37*
38* @param placement The DataMatrix placement.
39* @param symbolInfo The symbol info to encode.
40* @return The bit matrix generated.
41*/
42static BitMatrix EncodeLowLevel(const BitMatrix& placement, const SymbolInfo& symbolInfo) {
43 int symbolWidth = symbolInfo.symbolDataWidth();
44 int symbolHeight = symbolInfo.symbolDataHeight();
45
46 BitMatrix matrix(symbolInfo.symbolWidth(), symbolInfo.symbolHeight());
47 int matrixY = 0;
48 for (int y = 0; y < symbolHeight; y++) {
49 // Fill the top edge with alternate 0 / 1
50 int matrixX;
51 if ((y % symbolInfo.matrixHeight()) == 0) {
52 matrixX = 0;
53 for (int x = 0; x < matrix.width(); x++) {
54 matrix.set(matrixX, matrixY, (x % 2) == 0);
55 matrixX++;
56 }
57 matrixY++;
58 }
59 matrixX = 0;
60 for (int x = 0; x < symbolWidth; x++) {
61 // Fill the right edge with full 1
62 if ((x % symbolInfo.matrixWidth()) == 0) {
63 matrix.set(matrixX, matrixY, true);
64 matrixX++;
65 }
66 matrix.set(matrixX, matrixY, placement.get(x, y) == 1);
67 matrixX++;
68 // Fill the right edge with alternate 0 / 1
69 if ((x % symbolInfo.matrixWidth()) == symbolInfo.matrixWidth() - 1) {
70 matrix.set(matrixX, matrixY, (y % 2) == 0);
71 matrixX++;
72 }
73 }
74 matrixY++;
75 // Fill the bottom edge with full 1
76 if ((y % symbolInfo.matrixHeight()) == symbolInfo.matrixHeight() - 1) {
77 matrixX = 0;
78 for (int x = 0; x < matrix.width(); x++) {
79 matrix.set(matrixX, matrixY, true);
80 matrixX++;
81 }
82 matrixY++;
83 }
84 }
85
86 return matrix;
87}
88
89Writer::Writer() :
90 _shapeHint(SymbolShape::NONE)
91{
92}
93
94BitMatrix
95Writer::encode(const std::wstring& contents, int width, int height) const
96{
97 if (contents.empty()) {
98 throw std::invalid_argument("Found empty contents");
99 }
100
101 if (width < 0 || height < 0) {
102 throw std::invalid_argument("Requested dimensions are invalid");
103 }
104
105 //1. step: Data encodation
106 auto encoded = HighLevelEncoder::Encode(contents, _shapeHint, _minWidth, _minHeight, _maxWidth, _maxHeight);
107 const SymbolInfo* symbolInfo = SymbolInfo::Lookup(Size(encoded), _shapeHint, _minWidth, _minHeight, _maxWidth, _maxHeight);
108 if (symbolInfo == nullptr) {
109 throw std::invalid_argument("Can't find a symbol arrangement that matches the message. Data codewords: " + std::to_string(encoded.size()));
110 }
111
112 //2. step: ECC generation
113 ECEncoder::EncodeECC200(encoded, *symbolInfo);
114
115 //3. step: Module placement in Matrix
116 BitMatrix placement = DefaultPlacement::Place(encoded, symbolInfo->symbolDataWidth(), symbolInfo->symbolDataHeight());
117
118 //4. step: low-level encoding
119 BitMatrix result = EncodeLowLevel(placement, *symbolInfo);
120
121 //5. step: scale-up to requested size, minimum required quite zone is 1
122 return Inflate(std::move(result), width, height, _quiteZone);
123}
